1️⃣ Open Terminal
Press:
Copy code

Ctrl + `
OR
Click Terminal → New Terminal
2️⃣ Make Sure You Are in the Correct Folder
Type:
Copy code

ls
You should see:
Copy code

ll1.c
If not, navigate to your project folder:
Copy code

cd compiler_toolkit
3️⃣ Compile the Program
Copy code

gcc ll1.c -o ll1
If there is no error, compilation is successful.
4️⃣ Run the Program
Copy code

./ll1
5️⃣ If gcc Is Not Installed (Run Once)
Copy code

sudo apt update
sudo apt install build-essential -y
Then compile again.
